{"video_id": "CPaYBnLBlsg", "title": "Srimad Bhagavatam I Srila Prabhupada I SB 1. 2 .5 I 27.11.2023", "speaker": "HDG Srila Prabhupada", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CPaYBnLBlsg", "duration": 1609, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 9.0, "text": " The following is a class on the Srimad-Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 9.0, "end": 13.0, "text": " First Canto, First Chapter, Text No. 5"}, {"start": 13.0, "end": 20.0, "text": " Given by His Divine Grace A. C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila Prabhupada"}, {"start": 20.0, "end": 26.0, "text": " Recorded on 31st July, 1972, in Glasgow, Scotland."}, {"start": 30.0, "end": 42.0, "text": " So, questioning about Kṛṣṇa and answering the question is Kṛṣṇa-kathā."}, {"start": 42.0, "end": 55.0, "text": " So here it is recommended that if we are constantly engaged in Kṛṣṇa-kathā, about Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 55.0, "end": 59.0, "text": " talking about Kṛṣṇa, questioning about Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 60.0, "end": 66.0, "text": " then ātmāṣu prakṛtati ."}, {"start": 66.0, "end": 78.0, "text": " We are hankering after peacefulness of our heart, peacefulness of our atmosphere."}, {"start": 78.0, "end": 86.0, "text": " So here it is recommended that simply by inquiring about Kṛṣṇa"}, {"start": 86.0, "end": 90.0, "text": " and taking answer of the question,"}, {"start": 90.0, "end": 100.0, "text": " both the questioner and the answer-giver, both will be pleased."}, {"start": 100.0, "end": 104.0, "text": " Jaya ātmāṣu prakṛtati."}, {"start": 104.0, "end": 108.0, "text": " Therefore Caitanya Mahāprabhu ordered,"}, {"start": 108.0, "end": 113.0, "text": " yāre dākṣa tāre kaha kṛṣṇa-apare."}, {"start": 113.0, "end": 118.0, "text": " The world is like the blazing fire in the forest,"}, {"start": 118.0, "end": 128.0, "text": " so this Kṛṣṇa-kathā, this Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement,"}, {"start": 128.0, "end": 132.0, "text": " will give them relief."}, {"start": 132.0, "end": 136.0, "text": " Jaya ātmāṣu prakṛtati."}, {"start": 136.0, "end": 141.0, "text": " And Vishuddha Gosvāmī says,"}, {"start": 141.0, "end": 146.0, "text": " your question is very pious question."}, {"start": 146.0, "end": 150.0, "text": " That's it, sādhu."}, {"start": 150.0, "end": 154.0, "text": " Because it is about Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 154.0, "end": 160.0, "text": " The question was, after the departure of Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 160.0, "end": 169.0, "text": " dharma, kaṁ, what is that, sarnā-gata,"}, {"start": 169.0, "end": 174.0, "text": " kārthaṁ, what is that?"}, {"start": 174.0, "end": 176.0, "text": " This is the inquiry."}, {"start": 176.0, "end": 178.0, "text": " The answer is given there."}, {"start": 178.0, "end": 181.0, "text": " Sir, your inquiry,"}, {"start": 181.0, "end": 188.0, "text": " Kṛṣṇa comes for re-establishing the principles of religion."}, {"start": 188.0, "end": 190.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 190.0, "end": 192.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 192.0, "end": 194.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 194.0, "end": 196.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 196.0, "end": 197.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 197.0, "end": 198.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 198.0, "end": 199.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 199.0, "end": 200.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 200.0, "end": 201.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 201.0, "end": 202.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 202.0, "end": 203.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 203.0, "end": 205.0, "text": " That's it."}, {"start": 205.0, "end": 215.0, "text": " Lillian means the order set by the Supreme Personality of God."}, {"start": 215.0, "end": 217.0, "text": " That is lillian."}, {"start": 217.0, "end": 222.0, "text": " You do like this, just like king's order,"}, {"start": 222.0, "end": 225.0, "text": " or the government order,"}, {"start": 225.0, "end": 228.0, "text": " do like this."}, {"start": 228.0, "end": 231.0, "text": " Loose and, does not,"}, {"start": 231.0, "end": 245.04, "text": " So that is dharma. If you follow the do's and do nots given by Kṛṣṇa, that is a lie."}, {"start": 245.24, "end": 248.86, "text": " You cannot manufacture it. That is bogus."}, {"start": 249.06, "end": 253.12, "text": " So munayam svayabhu kṛṣṇa-bhagavad-vī-loka-maṅgalam ."}, {"start": 253.12, "end": 262.5, "text": " This question, just like our Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement, is the same."}, {"start": 262.74, "end": 267.16, "text": " It is simply questioning about Kṛṣṇa and hearing the answer."}, {"start": 267.4, "end": 278.64, "text": " It is loka-maṅgalam. Anywhere this vibration will go on, there will be all auspicious, loka-maṅgalam."}, {"start": 278.94, "end": 283.08, "text": " Kṛṣṇa saṅkṣu, cīnātmā suprasūdhī."}, {"start": 283.88, "end": 291.18, "text": " Another feature is, Kṛṣṇa is all-attractive, therefore talks about Him is also attractive."}, {"start": 291.44, "end": 298.56, "text": " In our Kṛṣṇa book, there are so many topics about Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 298.88, "end": 310.88, "text": " Janma karma-mṛdivyam, about His birth, about His transference from real father's house to another foster father."}, {"start": 311.14, "end": 322.44, "text": " Then the attack by the demon upon Kṛṣṇa, kaṁsau, all these activities."}, {"start": 322.78, "end": 329.88, "text": " If we simply study and hear the Kṛṣṇa saṅkṣu-prasṇā, then we are liberated."}, {"start": 330.08, "end": 340.44, "text": " Without any doubt, our liberation is guaranteed simply by hearing about Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 341.54, "end": 343.58, "text": " Kṛṣṇa therefore comes, so many activities."}, {"start": 343.78, "end": 350.3, "text": " Na māṅg karmānī limpaṇṭhī na me kaṇva-pareśa-prihāḥ ."}, {"start": 350.5, "end": 355.98, "text": " Kṛṣṇa says that He has nothing to do. What He has to do?"}, {"start": 356.18, "end": 363.56, "text": " But still He is killing so many demons, He is giving protection to so many devotees,"}, {"start": 363.84, "end": 369.28, "text": " because He has come to reestablish what is religious principle."}, {"start": 369.28000000000003, "end": 377.58000000000004, "text": " So by His personal activities, He's telling, otherwise, Kṛṣṇa has nothing to do."}, {"start": 377.78000000000003, "end": 383.28000000000003, "text": " Nā mā rāma kṛṣṇaḥ . He is self-satisfied. He has nothing to do."}, {"start": 383.54, "end": 392.98, "text": " But to teach us, He comes. In this way we should live, from the very beginning of His childhood."}, {"start": 393.18, "end": 395.94000000000005, "text": " This is the first point."}, {"start": 395.94, "end": 399.74, "text": " Nāmi Conceived"}, {"start": 399.74, "end": 403.94, "text": " In this time, you have to learn more about the knowledge of the wisdom of the Buddha."}, {"start": 404.14, "end": 409.14, "text": " You need to learn how to understand the knowledge of the Buddha."}, {"start": 409.34, "end": 415.34, "text": " You need to understand the knowledge of the Buddha."}, {"start": 415.54, "end": 421.14, "text": " The Buddha is now one of the most spiritual beings."}, {"start": 421.34, "end": 424.44, "text": " He is the most spiritual being."}, {"start": 424.68, "end": 425.4, "text": " He is all-encompassing."}, {"start": 425.40000000000003, "end": 434.26000000000005, "text": " I am telling of the whole age, I mean, whole world's programming age."}, {"start": 435.08000000000004, "end": 439.22, "text": " Athāta brahma-jīgānta. Athā."}, {"start": 439.52000000000004, "end": 445.82000000000005, "text": " Now, this is the time for inquiring about the Absolute Truth."}, {"start": 446.02000000000004, "end": 449.64000000000004, "text": " This is the time, means, this human form of life."}, {"start": 450.22, "end": 452.64000000000004, "text": " Animals cannot inquire."}, {"start": 452.64, "end": 463.58, "text": " So therefore Vedānta Sutra says athā, athā, brahma-jīgānta, inquire about the Absolute Truth."}, {"start": 463.97999999999996, "end": 470.46, "text": " Brahma, brahmeti, paramātmeti, bhagavān eti sadyati."}, {"start": 471.46, "end": 477.28, "text": " The ultimate Absolute Truth is Kṛṣṇa, the person."}, {"start": 477.7, "end": 482.41999999999996, "text": " Paramātmā is plenary expansion."}, {"start": 482.64, "end": 488.38, "text": " And brahma, he is impersonal, effulgent."}, {"start": 488.88, "end": 498.41999999999996, "text": " So if one understands Kṛṣṇa by question and answer, then he understands the other three features."}, {"start": 498.74, "end": 507.38, "text": " But simply by understanding the impersonal feature, brahma effulgence, one cannot understand Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 507.58, "end": 512.54, "text": " Neither by understanding or seeing the Paramātmā,"}, {"start": 512.84, "end": 514.84, "text": " one can understand Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 515.04, "end": 520.14, "text": " To see the Paramātmā is the business of the yogis."}, {"start": 520.54, "end": 525.64, "text": " dhyānā-vasthita-tad-gatena-manuṣā patsyante saṁyam yogiḥ ."}, {"start": 525.84, "end": 536.64, "text": " Yogina, the yogi, they are trying to see Kṛṣṇa or Viṣṇu within their heart by meditation."}, {"start": 536.84, "end": 538.9399999999999, "text": " Meditation means this."}, {"start": 539.24, "end": 542.4399999999999, "text": " dhyānā-vasthita-tad-gatena-manuṣā ."}, {"start": 542.66, "end": 544.64, "text": " patsyante saṁyam yogiḥ ."}, {"start": 544.84, "end": 561.64, "text": " And the jñānīs, they want to stop the material varieties, make it impersonal, and marge into the existence of brahma effulgence."}, {"start": 562.04, "end": 571.84, "text": " But devotees, they do not, neither of them, neither they even want to be transferred to the Vaikuṇṭha-loka."}, {"start": 572.0400000000001, "end": 578.94, "text": " They are satisfied in any condition life, provided they have got the opportunity to serve Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 579.14, "end": 582.44, "text": " That is everything."}, {"start": 582.64, "end": 584.84, "text": " Oh, very good."}, {"start": 585.0400000000001, "end": 587.94, "text": " So how can one put a question in the air?"}, {"start": 588.14, "end": 593.84, "text": " If one has three fingers, how can one put a question in the air?"}, {"start": 594.0400000000001, "end": 598.84, "text": " If one has three fingers, he can only put a question in the air."}, {"start": 599.0400000000001, "end": 600.94, "text": " I mean, you can go on."}, {"start": 600.94, "end": 609.24, "text": " As he tortures"}, {"start": 609.44, "end": 615.0400000000001, "text": " Sāya, for in vain,"}, {"start": 615.24, "end": 620.0400000000001, "text": " I can only guests."}, {"start": 620.24, "end": 625.1800000000001, "text": " Then,"}, {"start": 625.22, "end": 630.1400000000001, "text": " when I die,"}, {"start": 630.14, "end": 659.58, "text": " Therefore, materialism means"}, {"start": 660.14, "end": 672.54, "text": " forgetfulness of Kṛṣṇa. Otherwise, there is no other existence as material."}, {"start": 672.9399999999999, "end": 683.58, "text": " Just like in dream. In dream, some way or other, we create an atmosphere."}, {"start": 684.06, "end": 689.8199999999999, "text": " But actually, there is no, a different atmosphere."}, {"start": 690.14, "end": 696.22, "text": " We are not in this animation. We create something."}, {"start": 696.54, "end": 705.02, "text": " So, we are made in this, in our creation world."}, {"start": 705.58, "end": 713.8199999999999, "text": " Finally, I want to tell you that I am a teacher, and I am a master, and I teach."}, {"start": 714.06, "end": 719.98, "text": " I am trying to teach. This I am also going to teach all the day."}, {"start": 720.54, "end": 731.02, "text": " And I decide what to teach."}, {"start": 731.66, "end": 739.5, "text": " I'm a master in this, in this body, in this body."}, {"start": 739.9, "end": 747.42, "text": " I'm a master of everything."}, {"start": 748.22, "end": 749.98, "text": " I accept everything."}, {"start": 750.14, "end": 780.12, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 780.14, "end": 805.08, "text": " Now the question is,"}, {"start": 805.08, "end": 809.78, "text": " how the foods and stores which is matter,"}, {"start": 810.14, "end": 811.5, "text": " become spiritual?"}, {"start": 812.38, "end": 813.38, "text": " Isn't that the question?"}, {"start": 814.56, "end": 817.48, "text": " We say one man is constructing"}, {"start": 817.48, "end": 819.12, "text": " this type of a building"}, {"start": 819.12, "end": 821.96, "text": " with wood and stone."}, {"start": 823.02, "end": 825.1999999999999, "text": " We say this is materialistic."}, {"start": 825.92, "end": 829.86, "text": " They can also challenge you"}, {"start": 829.86, "end": 835.04, "text": " that you are also interested in wood and stone"}, {"start": 835.04, "end": 838.52, "text": " and constructing a huge church or temple."}, {"start": 838.52, "end": 838.84, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 839.26, "end": 840.12, "text": " Why in your..."}, {"start": 840.12, "end": 841.0, "text": " Yes, spiritualism."}, {"start": 843.46, "end": 845.68, "text": " Now, you can compare."}, {"start": 846.78, "end": 848.62, "text": " This is spiritualism means"}, {"start": 848.62, "end": 851.74, "text": " in this stone and earth and wood"}, {"start": 851.74, "end": 853.16, "text": " you remember Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 853.9, "end": 856.26, "text": " I am constructing something for Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 857.42, "end": 858.86, "text": " Therefore it is spiritual."}, {"start": 859.9, "end": 861.44, "text": " So the conclusion is"}, {"start": 861.44, "end": 863.86, "text": " when we forget Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 864.52, "end": 865.78, "text": " that is materialistic."}, {"start": 866.5, "end": 869.5600000000001, "text": " And when we constantly remember Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 869.5600000000001, "end": 869.9, "text": " that is materialistic."}, {"start": 869.9, "end": 869.96, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 869.96, "end": 870.02, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.02, "end": 870.04, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.04, "end": 870.08, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.08, "end": 870.1, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.12, "end": 870.16, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.16, "end": 870.2, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.2, "end": 870.24, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.24, "end": 870.32, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 870.32, "end": 874.0, "text": " That is materialistic."}, {"start": 874.0, "end": 876.88, "text": " The materialists means"}, {"start": 876.88, "end": 880.52, "text": " they are thinking of sense gratification."}, {"start": 880.52, "end": 884.0600000000001, "text": " All these big, big buildings"}, {"start": 884.0600000000001, "end": 885.72, "text": " were constructed"}, {"start": 885.72, "end": 889.52, "text": " in your country, Edinburgh."}, {"start": 889.52, "end": 891.34, "text": " The idea was"}, {"start": 891.34, "end": 894.4, "text": " that we shall show something opulent,"}, {"start": 894.4, "end": 896.32, "text": " that we are very great nation."}, {"start": 896.32, "end": 897.96, "text": " We have got nice buildings,"}, {"start": 897.96, "end": 899.92, "text": " nice churches,"}, {"start": 899.9200000000001, "end": 901.72, "text": " nice roads,"}, {"start": 901.72, "end": 903.5200000000001, "text": " swapsa."}, {"start": 903.5200000000001, "end": 905.44, "text": " Everyone wants to be swapsa"}, {"start": 905.44, "end": 908.5200000000001, "text": " before his friends and relatives."}, {"start": 908.5200000000001, "end": 912.2, "text": " So this is materialism."}, {"start": 912.2, "end": 914.5200000000001, "text": " But the same thing done"}, {"start": 914.5200000000001, "end": 917.3600000000001, "text": " for the satisfaction of Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 917.3600000000001, "end": 920.0000000000001, "text": " that we shall construct this temple"}, {"start": 920.0000000000001, "end": 922.6800000000001, "text": " for Kṛṣṇa's inauguration."}, {"start": 922.6800000000001, "end": 925.4000000000001, "text": " We shall construct this building"}, {"start": 925.4000000000001, "end": 928.96, "text": " for providing devotees of Kṛṣṇa"}, {"start": 928.96, "end": 929.8000000000001, "text": " so that"}, {"start": 929.9200000000001, "end": 934.48, "text": " they may be able to chant Hare Kṛṣṇa mahā-mantra"}, {"start": 934.48, "end": 936.72, "text": " without any disturbance."}, {"start": 936.72, "end": 938.6400000000001, "text": " It appears the same thing,"}, {"start": 938.6400000000001, "end": 940.4000000000001, "text": " karma and bhakti."}, {"start": 940.4000000000001, "end": 945.2, "text": " But bhakti is always in relation with Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 945.2, "end": 950.2400000000001, "text": " and karma is always in relation with sense gratification."}, {"start": 950.2400000000001, "end": 957.5600000000001, "text": " Therefore the thing, the ingredient,"}, {"start": 957.5600000000001, "end": 959.3600000000001, "text": " is originally spiritual."}, {"start": 959.36, "end": 961.72, "text": " Because it is Kṛṣṇa's energy."}, {"start": 961.72, "end": 963.5600000000001, "text": " But ahaṁ mamṛti,"}, {"start": 963.5600000000001, "end": 967.28, "text": " when we try to"}, {"start": 967.28, "end": 971.4, "text": " impose our proprietorship,"}, {"start": 971.4, "end": 973.36, "text": " that is materialism."}, {"start": 973.36, "end": 977.32, "text": " Materialism means forgetfulness of Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 977.32, "end": 978.88, "text": " Otherwise there is no materialism."}, {"start": 978.88, "end": 982.2, "text": " Everything is Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 982.2, "end": 983.6800000000001, "text": " Then?"}, {"start": 983.6800000000001, "end": 987.04, "text": " Kṛṣṇa is everything."}, {"start": 987.04, "end": 988.32, "text": " Kṛṣṇa is our own destiny."}, {"start": 988.32, "end": 989.36, "text": " Master is praying to me."}, {"start": 989.36, "end": 990.64, "text": " He is our father, our son,"}, {"start": 990.64, "end": 992.6800000000001, "text": " and not just a part of the world."}, {"start": 992.6800000000001, "end": 994.12, "text": " Forgetting Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 994.12, "end": 995.28, "text": " we have created so many"}, {"start": 995.28, "end": 997.28, "text": " opposite questions and answers,"}, {"start": 997.28, "end": 998.96, "text": " so none of them are able to give us"}, {"start": 998.96, "end": 1000.96, "text": " the same satisfaction."}, {"start": 1000.96, "end": 1002.8000000000001, "text": " All of us, but Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 1002.8000000000001, "end": 1005.44, "text": " give Him the same satisfaction also."}, {"start": 1005.44, "end": 1006.5600000000001, "text": " So with regard to that,"}, {"start": 1006.5600000000001, "end": 1008.32, "text": " when we reach that end of our life,"}, {"start": 1008.32, "end": 1010.28, "text": " we must continue to question and answer"}, {"start": 1010.28, "end": 1011.64, "text": " and to ask Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 1011.64, "end": 1013.16, "text": " We cannot do this without Him."}, {"start": 1013.16, "end": 1014.6, "text": " We cannot pay His attention."}, {"start": 1014.6, "end": 1016.44, "text": " We cannot ask for creation."}, {"start": 1016.44, "end": 1017.72, "text": " Because of the shame of God,"}, {"start": 1017.72, "end": 1019.2, "text": " we have to deal with the questions"}, {"start": 1019.2, "end": 1021.24, "text": " and answers that are related to Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 1021.24, "end": 1023.76, "text": " We can derive the highest satisfaction"}, {"start": 1023.76, "end": 1025.24, "text": " once we are ready to carry"}, {"start": 1025.24, "end": 1027.48, "text": " this transcendental literature."}, {"start": 1027.48, "end": 1029.68, "text": " Once we learn the Śukra-gāsāsī"}, {"start": 1029.68, "end": 1030.8400000000001, "text": " and make it all relevant"}, {"start": 1030.8400000000001, "end": 1032.76, "text": " to all problems"}, {"start": 1032.76, "end": 1034.32, "text": " pertaining to social, political,"}, {"start": 1034.32, "end": 1036.04, "text": " or religious matters."}, {"start": 1036.04, "end": 1037.4, "text": " Śrīla Prabhupāda himself"}, {"start": 1037.4, "end": 1039.48, "text": " and Kṛṣṇa are the sons and daughters."}, {"start": 1039.48, "end": 1041.92, "text": " Now we can discuss"}, {"start": 1041.92, "end": 1043.92, "text": " question and answer"}, {"start": 1043.92, "end": 1046.88, "text": " how political situation"}, {"start": 1046.88, "end": 1048.28, "text": " can be improved"}, {"start": 1048.28, "end": 1049.8799999999999, "text": " by Kṛṣṇa consciousness."}, {"start": 1049.8799999999999, "end": 1051.6399999999999, "text": " Can anyone ask that?"}, {"start": 1051.6399999999999, "end": 1053.28, "text": " We'll answer this question."}, {"start": 1053.28, "end": 1054.44, "text": " Yes."}, {"start": 1054.44, "end": 1057.92, "text": " If the head of the country,"}, {"start": 1057.92, "end": 1060.76, "text": " if the community, the army,"}, {"start": 1060.76, "end": 1062.6399999999999, "text": " and the rulers,"}, {"start": 1062.6399999999999, "end": 1063.84, "text": " and the Christians,"}, {"start": 1063.84, "end": 1065.24, "text": " they say that"}, {"start": 1065.24, "end": 1066.8, "text": " our own voting"}, {"start": 1066.8, "end": 1068.8799999999999, "text": " for taking"}, {"start": 1068.8799999999999, "end": 1070.84, "text": " a killing,"}, {"start": 1070.84, "end": 1072.48, "text": " making a question"}, {"start": 1072.48, "end": 1073.76, "text": " and making a government"}, {"start": 1073.76, "end": 1074.92, "text": " so that people"}, {"start": 1074.92, "end": 1077.28, "text": " aren't forced to vote."}, {"start": 1077.28, "end": 1077.96, "text": " Hmm?"}, {"start": 1078.28, "end": 1079.28, "text": " What is that?"}, {"start": 1079.28, "end": 1085.68, "text": " What is that?"}, {"start": 1085.68, "end": 1088.72, "text": " We have not if that..."}, {"start": 1088.72, "end": 1091.44, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1091.44, "end": 1093.8799999999999, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1093.8799999999999, "end": 1095.16, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1095.16, "end": 1096.6, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1096.6, "end": 1097.96, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1097.96, "end": 1099.84, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1099.84, "end": 1101.92, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1101.92, "end": 1103.6, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1103.6, "end": 1105.48, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1105.48, "end": 1106.8799999999999, "text": " ."}, {"start": 1106.88, "end": 1108.88, "text": " Huh? Is it all right?"}, {"start": 1136.88, "end": 1163.88, "text": " This is social improvement, political improvement."}, {"start": 1163.88, "end": 1165.88, "text": " What is this social improvement?"}, {"start": 1166.88, "end": 1173.88, "text": " This social improvement will be that when people become Christian scholars,"}, {"start": 1173.88, "end": 1178.88, "text": " and receive leadership, they will be satisfied."}, {"start": 1178.88, "end": 1182.88, "text": " They will be able to simplify the lives of these people,"}, {"start": 1182.88, "end": 1187.88, "text": " and they will be able to become Japanese, and they will be able to perform."}, {"start": 1187.88, "end": 1194.88, "text": " The basic principle is that the Atma has to proceed socially,"}, {"start": 1194.88, "end": 1200.88, "text": " and the Atma has to proceed spiritually."}, {"start": 1200.88, "end": 1205.88, "text": " Every householder..."}, {"start": 1205.88, "end": 1208.88, "text": " Everyone is dissatisfied."}, {"start": 1208.88, "end": 1216.88, "text": " There is no, I mean to say, peaceful atmosphere between the husband and the wife,"}, {"start": 1216.88, "end": 1219.88, "text": " the son and the father."}, {"start": 1219.88, "end": 1222.88, "text": " We remain, of course, together."}, {"start": 1222.88, "end": 1224.88, "text": " But everyone is..."}, {"start": 1224.88, "end": 1227.88, "text": " There is a different opinion."}, {"start": 1227.88, "end": 1233.88, "text": " In your country, it is very practically experienced."}, {"start": 1233.88, "end": 1238.88, "text": " Nobody agrees with nobody."}, {"start": 1238.88, "end": 1243.88, "text": " Everyone has got his own opinion."}, {"start": 1243.88, "end": 1249.88, "text": " So in Kṛṣṇa center, even in Kṛṣṇa center, we are having different opinions,"}, {"start": 1249.88, "end": 1253.88, "text": " because we are accustomed to live like that."}, {"start": 1254.88, "end": 1260.88, "text": " But actually, if we are serious about serving Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 1260.88, "end": 1263.88, "text": " then there cannot be two people."}, {"start": 1263.88, "end": 1264.88, "text": " One of them."}, {"start": 1264.88, "end": 1266.88, "text": " How to serve Kṛṣṇa?"}, {"start": 1266.88, "end": 1275.88, "text": " So in family life, if we introduce this acca-vigraha-seva,"}, {"start": 1275.88, "end": 1283.88, "text": " every family can see Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa-vigraha, Lord Caitanya Mahāprabhu's photo, vigraha."}, {"start": 1283.88, "end": 1288.88, "text": " And as we are, whatever we are doing, center is Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 1288.88, "end": 1292.88, "text": " Similarly, everyone can do that."}, {"start": 1292.88, "end": 1296.88, "text": " That will solve all social problems."}, {"start": 1296.88, "end": 1301.88, "text": " Social problems, political problems, economic problems."}, {"start": 1301.88, "end": 1304.88, "text": " Economic problem, practically there is no economic problem."}, {"start": 1304.88, "end": 1312.88, "text": " Just like in London, they are throwing away tons of tomatoes."}, {"start": 1312.88, "end": 1315.88, "text": " It will be seed."}, {"start": 1315.88, "end": 1318.88, "text": " That is our clue."}, {"start": 1318.88, "end": 1322.88, "text": " God has given sufficient to eat."}, {"start": 1322.88, "end": 1328.88, "text": " But because there is strike, we have created a problem."}, {"start": 1328.88, "end": 1334.88, "text": " So if one is Kṛṣṇa conscious, what is this strike?"}, {"start": 1334.88, "end": 1339.88, "text": " Strike means they want money, more money, more money."}, {"start": 1339.88, "end": 1340.88, "text": " There is no end."}, {"start": 1340.88, "end": 1351.88, "text": " When I first came to America and New York, there was strike of the transport man."}, {"start": 1351.88, "end": 1354.88, "text": " All transports stopped."}, {"start": 1354.88, "end": 1358.88, "text": " The subway, the bus, everything."}, {"start": 1358.88, "end": 1364.88, "text": " People became so much in difficulty."}, {"start": 1364.88, "end": 1369.88, "text": " So without being Kṛṣṇa conscious, there is no end of social problems."}, {"start": 1369.88, "end": 1371.88, "text": " There is no end of self-justification."}, {"start": 1371.88, "end": 1374.88, "text": " Nobody knows."}, {"start": 1374.88, "end": 1379.88, "text": " But Kṛṣṇa conscious person, they are satisfied."}, {"start": 1379.88, "end": 1386.88, "text": " Even still in India, you will find this satisfaction by Kṛṣṇa conscious."}, {"start": 1386.88, "end": 1394.88, "text": " A poor man, practically very big income, but he is satisfied."}, {"start": 1394.88, "end": 1396.88, "text": " He is satisfied in this way."}, {"start": 1396.88, "end": 1399.88, "text": " He thinks, Kṛṣṇa has given me this much."}, {"start": 1399.88, "end": 1403.88, "text": " I must receive this much."}, {"start": 1403.88, "end": 1405.88, "text": " Kṛṣṇa has given me this much."}, {"start": 1405.88, "end": 1407.88, "text": " Why should I eat?"}, {"start": 1407.88, "end": 1418.88, "text": " And that is also recommendation of the śāsyas, that tasya-yoheta-pratyate tatha-vidah nanabhate yantra-matāṁ kare"}, {"start": 1418.88, "end": 1425.88, "text": " We should not waste our time for improving our economic policy."}, {"start": 1425.88, "end": 1428.88, "text": " That is already settled up."}, {"start": 1428.88, "end": 1432.88, "text": " So whatever Kṛṣṇa will do, that is all right."}, {"start": 1432.88, "end": 1442.88, "text": " Let me utilize my valuable time of this human form of life in chanting Hare Kṛṣṇa."}, {"start": 1442.88, "end": 1454.88, "text": " People will not agree to this, but actually if anyone wants peace of the mind, jñātmā-śutra-siddhanti, then this process will be allowed."}, {"start": 1455.88, "end": 1457.88, "text": " This is practical also."}, {"start": 1457.88, "end": 1459.88, "text": " There are many saintly persons."}, {"start": 1459.88, "end": 1466.88, "text": " They do not try where to go, where to take money, or where to eat."}, {"start": 1466.88, "end": 1469.88, "text": " They are busy in Kṛṣṇa consciousness."}, {"start": 1469.88, "end": 1472.88, "text": " If Kṛṣṇa sends some food, I shall eat."}, {"start": 1472.88, "end": 1474.88, "text": " Otherwise it doesn't matter."}, {"start": 1474.88, "end": 1475.88, "text": " I shall starve."}, {"start": 1475.88, "end": 1477.88, "text": " Then what is their determination?"}, {"start": 1477.88, "end": 1478.88, "text": " Spirit."}, {"start": 1478.88, "end": 1480.88, "text": " They do not go anywhere."}, {"start": 1480.88, "end": 1483.88, "text": " But Kṛṣṇa sends it, everything."}, {"start": 1483.88, "end": 1484.88, "text": " Just like Gīla Maṁgata."}, {"start": 1484.88, "end": 1486.88, "text": " Just like Gīla Maṁgata."}, {"start": 1486.88, "end": 1488.88, "text": " He was not going anywhere."}, {"start": 1488.88, "end": 1491.88, "text": " He was living in Vrndavana."}, {"start": 1491.88, "end": 1496.88, "text": " Kṛṣṇa personally was coming to give him something."}, {"start": 1496.88, "end": 1498.88, "text": " He became blind."}, {"start": 1498.88, "end": 1500.88, "text": " He could not see."}, {"start": 1500.88, "end": 1506.88, "text": " So Kṛṣṇa would come just like a boy."}, {"start": 1506.88, "end": 1510.88, "text": " Gīla Maṁgata, I think you are hungry."}, {"start": 1510.88, "end": 1512.88, "text": " Will you take some milk?"}, {"start": 1512.88, "end": 1514.88, "text": " I am not very good."}, {"start": 1514.88, "end": 1517.88, "text": " All right, so give me little milk."}, {"start": 1517.88, "end": 1518.88, "text": " Next day he comes."}, {"start": 1518.88, "end": 1521.88, "text": " Then he would ask, who is this boy?"}, {"start": 1521.88, "end": 1522.88, "text": " I cannot see."}, {"start": 1522.88, "end": 1526.88, "text": " He comes and gives me milk daily."}, {"start": 1526.88, "end": 1529.88, "text": " Yuga-kemaṁ bhāmaḥ ."}, {"start": 1529.88, "end": 1533.88, "text": " In the Bhagavad-gītā he said that,"}, {"start": 1533.88, "end": 1539.88, "text": " until the devotee is completely dependent upon me,"}, {"start": 1539.88, "end": 1542.88, "text": " I carry personally."}, {"start": 1542.88, "end": 1545.88, "text": " Whatever he needs."}, {"start": 1545.88, "end": 1548.88, "text": " Yuga-bhūṇāṁ vṛnda-kāmaḥ."}, {"start": 1548.88, "end": 1555.88, "text": " That one person is supplying all the necessities of all the living entities."}, {"start": 1555.88, "end": 1559.88, "text": " That is God."}, {"start": 1559.88, "end": 1562.88, "text": " God is not beggar."}, {"start": 1562.88, "end": 1566.88, "text": " God fulfills everyone's necessities."}, {"start": 1566.88, "end": 1569.88, "text": " Freshly carried."}, {"start": 1569.88, "end": 1571.88, "text": " So that is,"}, {"start": 1571.88, "end": 1575.88, "text": " people are unhappy by so-called economic development."}, {"start": 1575.88, "end": 1577.88, "text": " Everyone is competing."}, {"start": 1577.88, "end": 1580.88, "text": " They have no satisfaction."}, {"start": 1580.88, "end": 1581.88, "text": " Without God,"}, {"start": 1581.88, "end": 1584.88, "text": " godless civilization is created."}, {"start": 1584.88, "end": 1587.88, "text": " Unnecessary competition."}, {"start": 1587.88, "end": 1590.88, "text": " But if you become God-conscious,"}, {"start": 1590.88, "end": 1592.88, "text": " he'll be satisfied."}, {"start": 1592.88, "end": 1594.88, "text": " Jaya ātmāḥ sattva-śrīve."}, {"start": 1594.88, "end": 1598.88, "text": " The very, very, very basic principle of devotional service"}, {"start": 1598.88, "end": 1600.88, "text": " will make one happy."}, {"start": 1600.88, "end": 1602.88, "text": " When?"}, {"start": 1602.88, "end": 1603.88, "text": " When?"}, {"start": 1603.88, "end": 1604.88, "text": " When?"}, {"start": 1604.88, "end": 1605.88, "text": " Thank you."}]}